content: Very fun and relaxing. Mr. Mint is sssooo cute!
This game.sucled it bored a 5 year I deamn a refund for a waist of my time amd money!
Bought this for the little ones and it was extremely disappointing. Not worth the money!
This is not candy land, you guys completely changed how candy land is played and made it stupid. If this is your idea of a classic board game then you're in the wrong line of work.
Terrible game first off and second my bank account shows that yall pulled 5.99 off instead of 1.99 I'm definitely gonna need that refund cause I just got completely scammed.
I thought this would be like the original game, but it is not. Unhappy with this version.
If you are looking for a strategy game, or a challenge then this isn't for you! But if you want a relaxing walk through the magical candyland it's great! Very nice graphics!
Refund! Not worth it. Boring for my 6 year grandson. To charge a fee it should have been way more to this game than basically one level! Asking for my money back.

HUGE WASTE OF MY MONEY! I was so excited to see a Candyland app. I was made to believe it was just like the computer game I played as a child! I LOVED that game so much and was ready to pay whatever to share that joy and play it with my daughter. So I bought it on my phone and my daughters tablet so we could play at the same time. Only to have it take about 15 minutes and have it be garbage! Hasbro, seriously I would pay decent money to have the EXACT SAME 1999 interactive Candyland!
This is not Candy Land. In any way. Not worth the money. Should be a free game.

My kids were so excited to play this..... they were very let down. It is not very engaging and it was over in 5 turns. Literally took them less than 10 minutes to complete. Very disappointed and would not recommend wasting the $2.99
Awful. This game should have not been priced. It should be free. It be good if it didnt repeat all the time. The game sucks and def not worth $2.99
It's great! The only thing I dont like it keeps repeating it self

I think this is great if you are looking to teach a young child how to use a touch screen. However if you plan on getting this don't assume it's going to be same as the computer game from 20 something years ago. It's quite different. The majority of it is tap and swipe only. You have some matching and sorting, but that's it. Very short, which is good for the age group they are targetting here. Still very cute and well made for what they were trying to do with it

For what you get - 10 minutes of game time start to finish, single player only this game should be free. Not 2.99. Graphics are good but the two kiddos I downloaded this for couldn't play together. One watched the other one play the whole game (in 10 min) and was disappointed to find out when it was her turn that it was the exact same challenges. Just needs some improvement or needs to be free. Might be fun for younger kids.
